Viruses per host species (min contig coverage 30%).

rate_infection_wga=tapply(X = data_wga.long$cov, INDEX = list(data_wga.long$host_species, data_wga.long$virus), FUN = function(x){
  n=length(x)
  postives=sum(x>0.3)
  rate=postives/n
  return(rate)
  })

"Vesantovirus_D.mel",
"LbFV_L.b",

"Linvill_road_virus_D.sim")

Plot the relation between number of heritable virus ientified and number of isofemale line sampled

n_iso=as.numeric(unlist(lapply(strsplit(names(total), "/"), FUN = function(x){return(x[2])})))
total2=rbind(total, n_iso)

lm_droso=lm(total2["total",1:9]~total2["n_iso",1:9])
lm_para=lm(total2["total",10:14]~total2["n_iso",10:14])
col_para="brown"
col_droso="green"
plot(total2["n_iso",], total2["total",], type="n", xlab="n isofemale lines sampled", ylab="number of heritable  virus detected") ; points(total2["n_iso",1:9], total2["total",1:9], pch=1, col=col_droso) ; points(total2["n_iso",10:14], total2["total",10:14], pch=2, col=col_para);abline(lm_droso, col=col_droso, lty=1); abline(lm_para, col=col_para, lty=2) ;legend("topright",c("Parasitoids", "Hosts"), col = c(col_para, col_droso), pch = c(2,1))

Another way of testing :

n=unlist(lapply(strsplit(colnames(tab), "="), FUN=function(x){return(x[2])}))
n_samples=as.numeric(unlist(lapply(strsplit(n, "/"), FUN=function(x){return(x[1])})))
n_isofemales=as.numeric(unlist(lapply(strsplit(n, "/"), FUN=function(x){return(x[2])})))
n_viruses=apply(tab, 2, sum)
tab_other_test=data.frame((n_viruses), n_samples, n_isofemales)
names(tab_other_test)=c("n_viruses","n_samples", "n_isofemales")
tab_other_test$lifestyle="free-living"
tab_other_test$lifestyle[10:14]="parasitoid"

test by an anova controling for the number of pooled samples (n_samples)

lm=lm(formula = tab_other_test$n_viruses ~ tab_other_test$n_samples + tab_other_test$lifestyle)

Let’s import explanatory variables : host species, time, location

variables=strsplit(rownames(tab), "_")
variables=lapply(X = variables, FUN = function(x){
  species=x[1]
  location=x[2]
  year=x[3]
  season=x[4]
  res=data.frame(species, location, year, season)
  return(res)
}
  )

covariates=do.call(what = rbind.data.frame, variables)
covariates$species=as.factor(covariates$species)
